This paper deals with the analysis of wireless cellular systems, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of stochastic simulation and mathematical modeling, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the need for a systematic approach to mobile dropping, which can be considered a control system (cs.SY) problem. Finally, the paper uses simulation to validate the theoretical analysis, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and computer graphics (cs.GR).
